accessibility.text: The Government must increase Taxes by 500 in order to close a 2,000 Inflationary Gap
The Government must increase Taxes by 500 in order to close a 2,000 Inflationary Gap
If taxes increase by 500, Disposable Income decrease by 500 and Consumption decrease by 500 x MPC = 500 x 0.8 = 400
